  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PLANT 100 FRUIT TREES IN EACH SCHOOL</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will serve many undernourished children from poor homes who leave during school and lunch hours to the bush to search for fruits to eat, thereby missing classes and exposing them to hazards.We are Planting 100  trees in each of the 24 public primary and secondary schools in FCT to make fruits available and protect school communities from heatwave, wind and soil erosion. It will provide basic skills to students to mitigate climate change and land degradation while increasing awareness</narrative>
  </description>
